metadata.name: Fractured Time #143
metadata.description:
Composed of bent shards and twisted slivers, Fractured Time is an exploration of how we might visually perceive gravity's effects on linear time.

Like an astronaut who gets too close to a blackhole, how would we make sense of this four-dimensional time-space experience? The pieces of the world as we know it would no longer align. Everything would stretch, splinter, pulse, and fray around us.

This is my attempt to capture that mind-bending trip in two dimensions.

Press [s] to save a .png at 4000 x 4000 pixels
Press [f] to open fullscreen

32 Color Palettes

metadata.name: Urban Jungle #145
metadata.description:
A riot of colors and shapes that blend urban art with natural elements. The trees and vibrant hues, seem to burst out of the concrete jungle, challenging the viewer's perception of the boundary between the city and nature. 

Elements are incorporated into the piece, adding to the overall sense of chaos and energy. Despite the seeming discordance, the composition is unified by the use of color and movement. 

"Urban Jungle" captures the raw and untamed spirit of the city, reminding us that even amidst the chaos, there is a kind of beauty to be found.

=================

Press "s" to save

Press "2" to export - 3614 × 4800
Press "3" to export - 7228 × 9600
Press "4" to export - 9036 × 12000

@gpitombo, May 2023
